jobContext:
Handle regular procurement activities, such as Pay Order issuance, floating RFQ, negotiation, approval, and contract management for IT and Non-IT Capex, Opex, and service procurements;
    Ensure value for money and cost saving for all purchases;
    Handle periodic procurement activities, such as enlistment, evaluation, and audit;
    Actively participate in process automation and digitization activities through regular UAT in Oracle EBS and fusion;
    Ensure legal, regulatory, organizational, and ethical compliance and transparency are strictly met as per policy;
    Support for audit requirements, regulatory requirements, compliance, and governance;
    Internal and external stakeholder management and supplier performance and relationship management;
    Ensure that UPC and agreements are renewed on time and initiate the process;
    Clarification, preparation, and execution of negotiation;
    Bill processing and forwarding to payments;
    Documentation, all sorts of procurement-related reporting, and information preserving.
